        <div n="662-100M" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-662-100M-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-100M-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-100M-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-662-100M-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-100M-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-100M-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-662-100M-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-662-100M-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-100M-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-662-100M-line-1"> Poor Ladies! tho' their business be to Play,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-662-100M-line-2"> 'Tis hard, they must be Busy Night and Day,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-662-100M-line-3"> Why shou'd they want y<hi rend="sup">eÌ£</hi> Priviledge of Men</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-662-100M-line-4"> Nor take some small Diversions now &amp; then?</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-662-100M-line-5"> Had Women, been the Makers of Our Laws,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-662-100M-line-6"> And why they were not, I can see no Cause?</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-662-100M-line-7"> The Men should slave at Cards from Morn to Night.</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-662-100M-line-8"> And Female Pleasures be to Read and Write.</l></lg></div>
      </div>
